race.comment: SHOW SOME DECORUM (5) wasn't disgraced in town last start, sticking on gamely into midfield. He now drops back to a trip he relishes, has had a month between runs, and importantly gets weight relief. Fourth-up, he looks well placed to break a long run of outs. SPANISH FOX (4) resumes in a suitable assignment and has the tactical speed to offset the wide draw. His Sydney form reads well for this level, and with a solid trial under his belt, he rates a leading player fresh. SCUD (14) is holding his form nicely, winning at Port Macquarie two back before a solid fourth at Doomben. He has a good record at this track and remains among the key chances. KING OF NAPLES (10) hasn't won for some time but continues to race well and has been kept fresh for this. Capable of striking. RALPHIE (11) gets back but owns a sharp turn of foot. Massive danger if the tempo is strong.
